Configure Github actions build

This config should be pretty much the same as the pre-existing Travis
build.

For example I have disabled the `fail-fast` flag as this mirrors the
existing behaviour of the Travis build (if one version of ruby fails
then the other builds will continue).

I ran into issues getting the ruby 1.9.3 build running. Upgrading
rubygems fixed this issue, however prior to ruby 2.3.0 you need to
specify the exact version (meaning you can't just run `gem update
--system`).

In order to address this issue I have added the rubygems version to the
build matrix, note that for rubies >= 2.3.0 the version number isn't
present which means it will install the latest version.

I have also included a check ruby version step which should make it
easier to debug builds.

Prepare for 0.16.2 release

Fix regression introduced by frozen symbol fix

There was a recent change [1] made to how punctuation is escaped to address
an issue introduced by a proposal in Ruby 2.7 (which is to change the
behaviour of `Symbol#to_s` so that it returns a frozen string) [2].

This ended up breaking support for calling the `memoize` method with a
punctuated string [3], e.g.

```ruby
class Dog
  extend Memoist

  def woof?
    true
  end

  memoize 'woof?'
end
```

I have added an additional test which should prevent further regressions
from being introduced.

[1] a893ce6
[2] https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/16150
[3] https://github.com/matthewrudy/memoist/issues/85
Prepare for 0.16.1 release

Generate CHANGELOG file

I am preparing a new release but first wanted to make sure that we had
somesort of changelog history.

I have ended up using `github-changelog-generator` to generate it using
PRs, it isn't perfect as it doesn't include commits which haven't been
merged via a PR but it is better than nothing :-).

Build travis against jruby-9.1.9.0

Travis was having issues with jruby 9.1.5.0 and so I have ended up
bumping the version of jruby 9.1 we're testing against to 9.1.9.0

Merge pull request #82 from casperisfine/mri-27-frozen-string

Make Memoist.escape_punctuation compatible with MRI 2.7

The latest ruby-2.7 preview included some changes to `Symbol#to_s` so that it returns a frozen string [1].

This PR fixes an issue with the `Memoist.escape_punctuation` method so that we can maintain compatibility with this new behaviour potentially being introduced in Ruby 2.7.

[1]  https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/16150
